		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I tried writing some spc700 code to see how long it takes to make a square wave in software, and I got this:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">ldw {phase_0}&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;//5<br />adw {frequency_0}&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;//5 10<br />stw {phase_0}&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;//5 15<br />cpy {duty_0}&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;//3 18<br />bcs +&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;//2 20<br />adc {output}={volume_0}&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;//6 26<br />+;<br /></div><br /><br />Already 26 cycles, and the spc700 only has 32 cycles between samples. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt=":roll:" title="Rolling Eyes" /><br /><br />Maybe doing two samples at once would be a little bit better.

		

